						               													<description>From the back of the book:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;The years since the Truce of Tukayyid have given rise to a new breed of war machines. The break in hostilities has allowed both the Inner Sphere and the Clans to expand their arsenals, creating bold new 'Mech designs tailored specifically to the enemy. When war resumes, these new machines will dominate the front lines in the struggle for the fate of humanity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BattleTech Record Sheets 3055 &amp;amp; 3058 provides more than 250 filled-out record sheets for the BattleMechs, tanks, hovercraft and VTOLS described in BattleTech Technical Readouts 3055 and 3058, including variants and alternate configurations. As an added feature, the game information for the relevant weapons and equipment is printed on each record sheet for easy reference.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;User comment:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One of the largest of the record sheet packs produced by FASA, this pack was square-bound - making it diffiult to photocopy any of the record sheets without breaking or removing the spine of the book. On the other hand, the sheets included the weapon information for each 'Mech, and the pack includes everything from the two Tech Readouts - not just 'Mechs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
